README

INTRODUCTION

This is a simple example for ZMQ's request-reply sockets in python. The application consists of a simple server-client setup. 
The server is launched and the client connects to it at a pre-assigned port.
The client requests and sends the message "Hello" to the server, and the server replies with the message 'World from Hello'
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
PRE-REQUISITES

In order to run this application, the latest stable version of ZeroMQ along with the python language bindings need to be installed 
in all the machines deploying this application. The full instructions for installation can be found in:

ZeroMQ
http://zeromq.org/intro:get-the-software

Python-ZeroMQ bindings:
http://zeromq.org/bindings:python

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
DEPLOYMENT

To deploy this application:-

1. Launch the server either as:-
	
		python server.py <port_no>				(assuming the host is localhost)
		
	OR
		python server.py <host_name> <port_no>
		
2. Once the server is live, launch the client application either as:-
		
		python client.py <port_no>				(assuming the host is localhost)
		
	OR
		python client.py <host_name> <port_no>
		

